					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'm having problems setting the scroll values mid-scanline, can someone tell me what I'm doing wrong? It works fine if SCROLL_X and SCROLL_Y are #0, but anything else and I get weird results (for example, after a certain point SCROLL_X scrolls in both X and Y). I'm trying to do the $2006, $2005, $2005, $2006 trick.<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp;; Set scroll, adding current scanline<br />&nbsp; lda PPUSTATUS&nbsp; &nbsp;; reset scroll status<br />&nbsp; <br />&nbsp; ; In-scanline scroll = PPUADDR,PPUSCROLL,PPUSCROLL,PPUADDR<br />&nbsp; ; ((Y &amp; %11000000) &gt;&gt; 6) | ((Y &amp; %00000011) &lt;&lt; 4) | (N &lt;&lt; 2)<br />&nbsp; ; Simplified to just (N &lt;&lt; 2)<br />&nbsp; lda #%00000100<br />&nbsp; sta PPUADDR <br />&nbsp; <br />&nbsp; ; X<br />&nbsp; lda SCROLL_X<br />&nbsp; sta PPUSCROLL<br />&nbsp; <br />&nbsp; ; Y<br />&nbsp; lda SCROLL_Y<br />&nbsp; adc #32&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; Add current scanline+1 to scroll<br />&nbsp; sta PPUSCROLL<br />&nbsp; <br />&nbsp; ; ((X &amp; %11111000) &gt;&gt; 3) | ((Y &amp; %00111000) &lt;&lt; 2)<br />&nbsp; ; Compute munged Y<br />&nbsp; and #%00111000<br />&nbsp; asl <br />&nbsp; asl<br />&nbsp; sta HBLANK_TEMP ; Store munged Y in Temp<br />&nbsp; lda SCROLL_X<br />&nbsp; lsr<br />&nbsp; lsr<br />&nbsp; lsr<br />&nbsp; <br />&nbsp; ora HBLANK_TEMP ; Or munged X with munged Y<br />&nbsp; sta PPUADDR<br /></div><br /><br />I understand it's not optimized as it can be (and I'm eventually going to move the scroll-pos munging out of there, since this code is in the middle of scanline drawing), I'm just trying to get it to work first.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

