						<div class="postbody">Is there some reason you're trying to find the hardest way to do everything? Zelda didn't need MMC5 or use complicated scrolling tricks. Learning how to use them is cool and all, but it can also be a form of procrastination. One way artists spark creativity is to force some kind of limitation... Today I'm only going to use blues. Embrace the limitations, say to yourself, &quot;I can make it work with only 4 palettes for background&quot; <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br /><br />&quot;Procrastination&quot; because you spend all your time solving technical problems rather than programming your game.</div>

					
