						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Kasumi wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">1.70 MB gif of what ROM City Rampage's HUD/Nametable updating looks like: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://i.imgur.com/pP6VDps.gif">http://i.imgur.com/pP6VDps.gif</a><!-- m --></div><br />Looks like the Crystalis trick to me. If you pause, you can see that whatever is right above and right below the status bar in the name table connect directly in the final render. Also notice that there's a blank row above the status bar in the final render, so that the gameplay window can scroll smoothly without glitches.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">dougeff wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Crystalis is a great example, but it does have those attribute table glitches I mentioned. And a nice big line of a glitch, right at the split screen.</div><br />Yeah, lots of commercial games were glitchy. The technique is perfectly valid, though, you just have to time it right.</div>

